Predicting whether a water source actually has water available

Our modeling goal is to predict whether a water source actually has water available at it, based on characteristics of the water source observed during a visit. Lets start by reading in the data.

Explore Data

Transform data

water <- water_raw  %>%
    filter(status_id %in% c("y", "n"),
           country_name == "Sierra Leone", 
           lon_deg < 0, lat_deg < 20, lat_deg > 0) %>%
    mutate(pay = case_when(
        str_detect(pay, "^Yes") ~ "yes",
        str_detect(pay, "^No") ~ "no",
        is.na(pay) ~ pay,
        TRUE ~ "it's complicated"
    )) %>%
    select(-country_name, -status, -report_date) %>%
    mutate(across(where(is.character), as.factor))

Build a model

Split data

library(tidymodels)
##  Attaching packages  tidymodels 1.0.0 
##  broom        1.0.1      rsample      1.1.1
##  dials        1.1.0      tune         1.0.1
##  infer        1.0.4      workflows    1.1.2
##  modeldata    1.0.1      workflowsets 1.0.0
##  parsnip      1.0.3      yardstick    1.1.0
##  recipes      1.0.3
##  Conflicts  tidymodels_conflicts() 
##  scales::discard() masks purrr::discard()
##  dplyr::filter()   masks stats::filter()
##  recipes::fixed()  masks stringr::fixed()
##  dplyr::lag()      masks stats::lag()
##  yardstick::spec() masks readr::spec()
##  recipes::step()   masks stats::step()
##  Dig deeper into tidy modeling with R at https://www.tmwr.org
set.seed(123)

water_split <- initial_split(water, strata = status_id)
water_train <- training(water_split)
water_test  <- testing(water_split)

set.seed(234)
water_folds <- vfold_cv(water_train, strata = status_id)
library(usemodels)
usemodels::use_ranger(status_id ~ ., data = water_train)
## ranger_recipe <- 
##   recipe(formula = status_id ~ ., data = water_train) 
## 
## ranger_spec <- 
##   rand_forest(mtry = tune(), min_n = tune(), trees = 1000) %>% 
##   set_mode("classification") %>% 
##   set_engine("ranger") 
## 
## ranger_workflow <- 
##   workflow() %>% 
##   add_recipe(ranger_recipe) %>% 
##   add_model(ranger_spec) 
## 
## set.seed(74403)
## ranger_tune <-
##   tune_grid(ranger_workflow, resamples = stop("add your rsample object"), grid = stop("add number of candidate points"))
library(themis)

ranger_recipe <- water %>%
    recipe(status_id ~ ., data = water_train) %>%
    update_role(row_id, new_role = "id") %>%
    step_unknown(all_nominal_predictors()) %>%
    step_other(all_nominal_predictors(), threshold = 0.03) %>%
    step_impute_linear(install_year) %>%
    step_downsample(status_id)

ranger_spec <- 
  rand_forest(trees = 1000) %>% 
  set_mode("classification") %>% 
  set_engine("ranger") 

ranger_workflow <- 
  workflow() %>% 
  add_recipe(ranger_recipe) %>% 
  add_model(ranger_spec) 

doParallel::registerDoParallel()

set.seed(74403)
ranger_rs <-
  fit_resamples(ranger_workflow, 
                resamples = water_folds, 
                control = control_resamples(save_pred = TRUE))

Model evaluation

Show performance

collect_metrics(ranger_rs)
## # A tibble: 2  6
##   .metric  .estimator  mean     n std_err .config             
##   <chr>    <chr>      <dbl> <int>   <dbl> <chr>               
## 1 accuracy binary     0.893    10 0.00139 Preprocessor1_Model1
## 2 roc_auc  binary     0.951    10 0.00101 Preprocessor1_Model1
collect_predictions(ranger_rs) %>%
    group_by(id) %>%
    roc_curve(status_id, .pred_n) %>%
    autoplot()

conf_mat_resampled(ranger_rs, tidy = FALSE) %>%
    autoplot()

Finalize workflow (last_fit)

final_fitted <- last_fit(ranger_workflow, water_split)

collect_metrics(final_fitted)

Variable importance

library(vip)
## 
## Attaching package: 'vip'
## The following object is masked from 'package:utils':
## 
##     vi
imp_data <- ranger_recipe %>%
    prep() %>% bake(new_data = NULL) %>%
    select(-row_id)

ranger_spec %>%
    set_engine(engine = "ranger", importance = "permutation") %>%
    fit(status_id ~ ., data = imp_data) %>%
    vip(geom = "point")

imp_data %>%
    pivot_longer(c(installer, pay, water_tech)) %>%
    ggplot(aes(y = value, fill = status_id)) +
    geom_bar(position = "fill") +
    facet_grid(rows = vars(name), scales = "free_y", space = "free_y") +
    theme(legend.position = "top") +
    scale_fill_brewer(type = "qual", palette = "Set2") +
    scale_x_continuous(expand = expansion(mult = c(0, 0)), labels = scales::percent) +
    labs(
    x = "% of water sources", y = NULL, fill = "Water available?",
    title = "Water availability by source characteristic in Sierra Leone",
    subtitle = "Water sources with no payment information are likely to have no water available"
  )
